WEBVTT

00:08.360 --> 00:12.000
Hi there! Welcome to
this video where we

00:12.000 --> 00:14.240
are going to learn
about cyberbullying.

00:14.780 --> 00:17.180
The goal of the
presentation is to

00:17.180 --> 00:18.560
help you to
understand what

00:18.560 --> 00:21.160
cyberbullying is,
what motivates people

00:21.160 --> 00:24.440
to do it, and how to
recognise it. In the

00:24.440 --> 00:26.720
video, firstly, we
will look at what

00:26.720 --> 00:29.120
cyberbullying is,
then we will look at

00:29.120 --> 00:31.100
some examples of
cyberbullying and

00:31.100 --> 00:33.280
what to do if you are
being cyberbullied.

00:36.160 --> 00:40.060
What is cyberbullying
? Cyberbullying is

00:40.060 --> 00:41.920
bullying that takes
place through digital

00:41.920 --> 00:44.880
devices and online
platforms. It

00:44.880 --> 00:47.180
involves sending,
posting or sharing

00:47.180 --> 00:50.480
negative, harmful,
false or mean content

00:50.480 --> 00:52.800
about someone else,
often with the intent

00:52.800 --> 00:55.500
to embarrass, harass
or hurt them.

00:58.200 --> 01:01.080
Common forms include
sending threatening

01:01.080 --> 01:03.820
or insulting messages
through text, social

01:03.820 --> 01:06.980
media or gaming
platforms. Spreading

01:06.980 --> 01:09.280
rumours or sharing
embarrassing photos

01:09.280 --> 01:11.500
or videos without
consent.

01:11.740 --> 01:14.060
Impersonating someone
online to damage

01:14.060 --> 01:17.060
their reputation.
Excluding someone

01:17.060 --> 01:19.140
from online groups or
activities

01:19.140 --> 01:21.680
deliberately.
Creating fake

01:21.680 --> 01:24.240
profiles to harass
someone. Publicly

01:24.240 --> 01:26.340
posting hurtful
comments or personal

01:26.340 --> 01:27.370
information.

01:30.550 --> 01:32.250
What makes
cyberbullying

01:32.250 --> 01:33.930
particularly harmful
compared to

01:33.930 --> 01:35.990
traditional bullying
is that it can happen

01:35.990 --> 01:39.310
24 7, reach a wide
audience quickly, be

01:39.310 --> 01:41.550
difficult to delete
once posted, and

01:41.550 --> 01:43.270
sometimes allows
bullies to remain

01:43.270 --> 01:46.650
anonymous. Victims
may feel like there's

01:46.650 --> 01:48.410
no escape since it
follows them into

01:48.410 --> 01:51.390
their homes and
private spaces. If

01:51.390 --> 01:53.770
you or someone you
know is experiencing

01:53.770 --> 01:56.130
cyberbullying, it's
important to do the

01:56.130 --> 01:58.770
following things.
Keep a record of the

01:58.770 --> 02:01.310
harassment, for
example, screenshots.

02:01.310 --> 02:03.990
Block the person.
Report it to the

02:03.990 --> 02:07.370
platform. Talk to a
trusted adult, school

02:07.370 --> 02:09.870
counsellor or
authority figure.

02:09.870 --> 02:12.010
Many schools and
workplaces have

02:12.010 --> 02:14.150
specific policies
against cyberbullying

02:14.150 --> 02:16.730
, and in severe cases
, it can have legal

02:16.730 --> 02:20.450
consequences.